 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Head of Macroeconomics The Economist Newspaper Limited New York, NY 10017 Introduction: 
The Economist Intelligence Unit (EIU) helps leaders prepare for opportunity, empowering them to act with confidence when making strategic decisions. The EIU is the global standard in providing quality, actionable intelligence to the public and private sector, assessing issues that impact the marketplace for over two hundred countries. 
We are recruiting for a Head of Macroeconomics. This role is one of the most senior intellectual and analytical roles in the EIU, ensuring that our forecasts are the best available for decision-makers. You will manage a small team of senior analysts who ensure global consistency of the work of our wider team, and also manage our Economics and Data Unit. 
 You would be expected to have influence over a much larger team of analysts, while also being a leading communicator of our forecast to clients and the wider public. You would also be able to drive innovation and quality in our quantitative methods covering macroeconomic forecasting, risk measurement, policy assessment and emerging new techniques. 
This opportunity can be located in NY, Washington DC or London 
Accountabilities:
 
How you will contribute: 
Directly manage a small team of senior analysts and, through them, a larger team of quantitative analysts; indirectly mentor and influence a wider team of economic, political and business analysts 
Directly and through your team drive incorporation of key global trends and narratives into our forecasts, working effectively through a matrix structure 
Proactively implement improvements in our forecasting techniques and methods, both incremental and systematic 
Write articles on key global and economic themes for our clients and ensure generation of these throughout your team 
Directly, and indirectly through your team, implement a program of continuous learning and development for analysts 
Build the external profile of the EIU, including through building our business of paid speaking engagements 
Work with analysts in other teams to test conclusions and ensure consistency 
Be an internal and external thought leader for our forecasts and analysis, ensuring our content is relevant, insightful and actionable 
Brief clients, present at conferences, and do media interviews 
Ensure adherence to Economist editorial guidelines, including independence, objectivity and quality 
Experience, skills and professional attributes:
 
The ideal skills for this role are: 
Deep knowledge of modeling, statistics and econometrics; ideally including familiarity with the potential role of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning techniques in economic forecasting 
Strong credibility on global macroeconomics, through some combination of significant work experience and postgraduate qualifications (PhD desirable) 
Be a dynamic and experienced presenter, ideally with an existing public profile and media experience 
Comfortable using an influencing management style and can achieve outcomes without direct line management authority 
Highly developed skills in managing an intellectually-driven team 
Fluency in English, exceptional writing skills. The Economist Newspaper Limited 30+ days ago original job Report job Apply Now Apply On Company Site Save this job Save this job Jobs at The Economist Newspaper in New York, NY Company Info Follow Get job updates from The Economist Newspaper Limited Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume Hiring Lab Career Advice Browse Jobs Browse Companies Salaries Find Certifications Indeed Events Work at Indeed Countries About Help Center Â© 2021 Indeed Do Not Sell My Personal Information Accessibility at Indeed Privacy Center Cookies Privacy Terms Let Employers Find You Upload Your Resume 
 
 
 
 
 
